rComments: Very detailed, but laid back. He is an easy prof teaching a difficult subject. Goes over things well and will answer any question you have. Humble, expects class to call him out if he gets something wrong. I recommend trying to do research work with him as well (if you can).

It is important to take notes during lectures so you will understand the slides later. definitely use the text book to go over any thing you do not understand, because most of the lecture material can be found in the text book.  It is not an easy A but if you put in the effort an A is definitely possible
The lectures are difficult to follow but he is one of the most helpful professors outside of the classroom that I've ever had.

He thinks he's talking to fellow geneticists. It's impossible to pay attention during lectures because no matter how hard you try you just can't understand him. If he would only tone down the language the class would be so easy.
